I like shooting weddings. Lotta photographers would cringe at the prospect, but not me. I’m a fan. They’re like a multidisciplinary photo marathon, always keeping you on your toes (like a ballerina). Gotta be good at shooting portraits, candids, fashion, etc. as well as adapting to ever changing spaces and lighting conditions, all while navigating the family dynamics of people you’ve probably never met before. It’s a blast. Plus I get a free meal and a wad of cash at the end of the night. 

One time, a fancy couple tried to feed me Subway while their guests ate like kings. That one sucked.

As I post this I am actively wearing an anklet. I think we can all agree that’s pretty cool and fashion forward of me. 
Wanna know who else is cool and fashion forward? THE @zoelisterjones. Yeah, I said it.
